Clearly not. The creature merely whistled and tried to charge straight at Thassalin. Fortunately, despite its size, he was sufficiently agile to avoid it, but Nyssi couldn't help screaming when she nearly lost her grip on his too smooth scales.
"HOW DO YOU KILL THEM? ", cried Nyssi.
"TARGET THEIR HEADS! "
"THIS ISN'T GOING TO BE EASY! "
Thassalin blew out a breath, then circled around to approach the mountain he called home. The black beast followed, somewhat frightened when a bolt of fire struck it from behind. The creature hadn't noticed it wasn't alone anymore. Its fear grew as Thassalin slowed down, then struck the back of its head with his tail, causing it to veer off course.
Grunting and whistling, the creature took to the air and spat into the sky. Suddenly, everything turned black, as if the monster was sucking the light from the sky and replacing it with a perpetual cloud of night.
With no visibility left, Thassalin tried to retreat, but crashed into the treetops before landing in the clearing. As if it knew exactly where he had fallen, the creature charged right at him, dragging the dark cloud behind it.
"Kayel!" Tenuk exclaimed as he emerged from the cloud and began circling to try and spot Nyssi and Thassalin below in the darkness. "What do we do, Kayel? Kayel... ? Kayel, where are you?"
Below, Nyssi struggled to get up. She was certain she had hurt something, but her strange non-natural healing powers had already begun to take effect. That couldn't be said for Thassalin, who lay on a heap, leaning against the only tree that hadn't bent under his weight. Nyssi did her best to reach Thassalin, but she couldn't see two meters in front of her. Everything was plunged into darkness, swallowed by the malevolent shadows. And in those shadows, something howled.
A horrible staff-like tail came crashing down next to Nyssi, knocking her backward. However, she noticed that the tail was swaying without aiming at her. From what Nyssi could see and hear of the creature, it was growling and scratching the shadows it had created. Something was teleporting through the darkness, striking the monster, disorienting it.
A shot rang out suddenly, and the monster collapsed silently, inert. The darkness surrounding them dissipated, revealing what had happened. Standing on top of the creature was Kayel, gun in hand and breathing heavily.
"This... is the strangest shadow leap I've ever made... Thanto kat'olon..." panted Kayel. His eyes glowed with a black light, and dark energy coursed through his body. However, as he spoke, Kayel's organic armor regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow hue.
It took Nyssi a moment to understand what had happened. They all knew that Kayel possessed strange powers of shadow. He rarely used them because most people considered them impious and rather terrifying. But Nyssi did not know that Kayel could use these powers in the dark. And, judging by his behavior, Kayel seemed just as surprised himself.
"Are you okay?" Nyssi couldn't help asking.
"Yes, I'm fine. I killed something. It will be better in a minute." Kayel examined his work as Tenuk made his way down to land beside him, reverting to his normal Spast form.
Now that the creature was no longer moving, they could see what it was better. Its skin was black as coal and sticky, but the saliva continued to adhere to its body. It had four wings and four limbs, all ending in long talons, and two straight horns grew from its skull.
Before Tenuk and Kayel could ask what this thing was, something screamed and burst out of a nearby bush. However, the beast did not have time to reach them, as a familiar vehicle crashed into its side, sending it sprawling at Nyssi's feet. Without any hesitation, she grabbed her rifle and immediately shot it in the head, killing the creature on the spot.
"Oops...", muttered Retvik from the driver's seat, before clumsily turning off the engine and jumping out of the truck. "I, uh, didn't mean to do that. Are you guys okay?"
"You almost missed all the action," regretted Tenuk. "Where were you?"
"You all left me behind. I came here as fast as I could," sighed Retvik. "Can we know what these disgusting things are?"
Retvik's inquiry received a response from Thassalin, who had just stood up. He was cut and scratched all over and seemed a bit disoriented, but he didn't appear to be too badly injured.
"YOU KILLED THE CORRUPTIDS! THE INFECTED MONSTERS. CREATURES LEFT HERE WHEN CORRUPTION ATTACKED YOUR GODS."
"You mean... the horrible god-monster we... helped kill?" stammered Tenuk.
"YES. EXACTLY. THERE MIGHT BE OTHERS, BUT I DIDN'T SUCCEED IN Hitting THEM IN THE HEAD. I'M LACKING A GUN. AND TWO AGAINST ONE, IT'S NOT FAIR, IS IT?" Thassalin approached Kayel and patted his head. "THANK YOU, LITTLE ONE. YOU REMIND ME OF MY OLD FRIEND ARKADIN. BUT LESS KILLER AND LESS ABLE TO KILL UNIVERSES."
"Uh... thanks... I guess," said Kayel with a shrug. "So, we're done here?"
Nyssi shrugged, then took out her camera to photograph the now dead animals. She then pulled out her favorite dagger, the one associated with the god of death, and began cutting off one of the creature's horns, before moving on to the other. But just as she finished, the creatures erupted in flames and quickly turned into piles of ash. The same thing happened to the horns that Nyssi had cut off.
"Well... it's both convenient and not convenient at all," she sighed. "At least I have the photos..."
